		<div id="comment_body_64640594">Because this is 'new' tech and a failure only 10 units in out of the planned 62 seems newsworthy.
<br> <br>
Also, broken or frayed fiberglass is nasty stuff. It's not just abrasive but pieces break off into your skin like splinters and continue the irritation until you remove it. Having this wash up where people are barefoot makes the beach unusable. You don't want to be swimming in it either, at best you have some skin irritation at worst it get's in your eye and does damage.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64640594">
