			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64640978"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64640978"><p><div class="quote"><p>17 yards is 50 feet. A cube 50 feet on each side.</p></div><p>Wow! That's some bad match. 17 *cubic* yards is a cube approximately 7.72 feet on a side. Let's walk through the math. A cubic yard is a three dimensional volume of 17 units, each of which is 3*3*3=27 cubic feet. So, 17 cubic yards is 459 cubic feet. To figure out how big a cube that is in feet, you just calculate 459 to the power of<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.33333 which is approximately 7.72 feet, and that will be the length of one side of the cube.<br>If we try to fit that in a 70 foot trailer like you propose (let's say the trailer<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64640978">

