			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64640762"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64640762">Wind is also intermittent, it's just not all lumped into one half of the day.  The only real consequence for solar vs. wind is that you need storage that gathers continually for half the day, then releases for half the day, while wind needs storage that can gather or release whenever needed in smaller blocs of time.  Solar probably wins that argument because it'll be easier to use hydro for storage.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64640762">

